==English==

===Etymology===
French ''[[péricarpe]]'', from Latin ''[[pericarpium]]'', from Greek [[περικαρπιον]] ‘pod, husk, shell’, from [[περι-]] + [[καρπος]] ‘fruit’.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/'pɛrɪkɑ:p/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#{{botany}} The outermost layer of a ripe [[fruit]] or [[ovary]].
# used figuratively
#:*'''1974''': He learned, afternoon after afternoon, how to edge her into delicious frenzies, how to tremble the clitoris, '''pericarp''', and tip. — Guy Davenport, ''Tatlin!''

